    <note>Shao(2) Yu [1440] XCB, 58.2a, 59.9b, 68.13b, 69.1a, 76.16a; Hunan TZ, 134.5a, Jiangxi TZ, 9.12a, 13b, and CBD identify him as the same person as Shao(2) Ye, whose great grandfather, Yue [20857], moved to Guiyang (modern Lianxian) from Jingzhao. Yu (Ye) died in office as prefect of Guangzhou in 1014 at age 63. The Lianzhou 978 jinshi, Shao(2) Yi in CBD, 2, 1321, has exactly the same zi as Yu (Ye) and was once prefect of Guangzhou and therefore was exacrtly the same person as Yu (Ye). SS, 426.5a-6b. CBD, 2, 1327-8.</note>
